[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	Request extra base license at startup to enable saving physical changes
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	in priority order from left to right. The allowed license names are:
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	"invs invsb vdixl"
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] [-log <prefix>]
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	Prefix for the .log, .cmd, and .logv files. If it has an extension,
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	only the prefix is used. For example, either '-log abc' or '-log abc.log'
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	will create abc.log abc.cmd and abc.logv files. If the .log file already
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	exists, an integer is appended to all the file names to make them unique
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	(e.g. abc.log2 abc.cmd2 abc.logv2).
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] [-no_gui]
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	Disable GUI and Tk support. GUI will not be available later in the
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	session.
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] [-no_logv]
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	Specifies that verbose log file will not be created.
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] [-no_cmd]
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	Specifies that verbose command file will not be created.
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] [-overwrite]
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	Overwrite an existing .log file (and associated .cmd, .logv files)
[05/23 04:08:44     14s] 	instead of adding an integer to make the files unique.
